        "geocode_query": "119 D Street SE",
        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Capitol Hill Charmer 1 Bedroom. Steps to the Capitol Building with Balcony 119 D Street, SE #3, Washington, DC 20003 This main-level charming one-bedroom unit is just steps from the United States Capitol Building and the Rayburn House Office Building. It features hardwood floors and a decorative fireplace in the living room with large windows to allow gleaming light in. The unit has a dining area that could be used as an office. The galley kitchen features great updated cabinetry. with a refrigerator, gas range, and dishwasher. The kitchen opens up to your own semi-private balcony that opens up to a large Garden brick courtyard patio for all the residents. The Bedroom is large enough for a queen-size bed with a closet. The bathroom features a vanity with a tub/shower. The laundry is conveniently located on the lower level of the building. Window A/C and radiator heat. Sq Ft unknown. TAKE A YOUTUBE VIDEO TOUR - https://youtu.be/eq86v_ZTZUU Close to all the restaurants and shops that Capitol Hill has to offer! 119 D Street Southeast has a Walk Score of 76 out of 100. This location is Very Walkable, so most errands can be accomplished on foot. It is a two-minute walk from the Blue Metrorail Blue Line, the Orange Metrorail Orange Line, and the Silver Metrorail Silver Line at the CAPITOL SOUTH METRO STATION stop. This location is in the Capitol Hill neighborhood in Washington, D.C. Nearby parks include Folger Park, Providence Park (X Park), and House East Fountain. Pets are welcomed on a case-by-case basis with a one-time pet fee of $250-cats and $450-dogs. 12-month minimum lease. No short-term leases. Unfurnished. Street parking only. All adult applicants must apply and pass a credit check/background check, as well as meet the income requirements. We accept and consider all sources of income towards qualification.. Tenant pays for gas, electric (+cable and internet). No Move-In Fees! Additional Resident Benefits Package (RBP) $30 per month. Co-signers are welcome. The application fee/credit check is $54 per person, and the application may be completed on our website. We accept and consider all sources of income. The first full month's rent, RBP Fee, security deposit equal to one month's rent, and pet fees, are due at lease signing. The building is professionally managed by Chatel Real Estate. Luxury Capitol Hill expertise brought to you by Craig Shireman, “Craig the Châtel Château Specialist” with Chatel Real Estate, Inc. Please contact for requests for showings by emailing show contact info , no phone calls please",
