        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Come home to a great community - Leo at Waterfront Station! Address: 1150 4th St SW Washington, DC 20024 Reach out via phone or text: show contact info Beds: Efficiency / Baths: 1 / Size: 395 sq ft Base monthly rent: $1489 Total Monthly Price: $1489 *Optional and usage-based charges not included. Our Southwest D.C. apartments were built to be environmentally friendly, with features and amenities inside and out that were carefully chosen to give you the lifestyle you deserve! Inside each home, you'll find stainless steel appliances, granite countertops with subway tile backsplashes, moveable kitchen islands with extra cabinets, and two finish options for kitchens! You'll appreciate the remote-operated bedroom ceiling fans, frameless glass-enclosed showers, floor-to-ceiling windows, expansive walk-in closets and full-size energy-efficient washers and dryers! Household income must be verified to match property income restrictions (50% AMI). Two most recent tax returns, six most recent bank statements for all accessible bank accounts and proof of all additional income is required (i.e. self-employment, recurring gifts, social security). If needed, other documentation may be requested. Deposit: Call Length of Lease: Variable Property Features: ❖ Chic clubroom ❖ Conference room space ❖ Dog-washing boutique ❖ Fitness classes ❖ Heated infinity edge pool on roof deck ❖ Outdoor patio with gas grill and fireplace ❖ Party room with bar and kitchen ❖ Yoga and aerobics space ❖ Full-service concierge ❖ Game room with pool table and multiple TVs ❖ Nearby Capital Bikeshare and Zipcar stations ❖ Rooftop deck with incredible views of D.C. and Virginia ❖ Shared workspace and Wi-Fi lounge ❖ State-of-the-art fitness center with cardio and weightlifting machines ❖ Steps to the Waterfront Metro station on the Green Line ❖ Underground controlled access parking Apartment Amenities: ❖ 24/7 fitness center with studio ❖ Attached garage parking ❖ Bike storage with repair station ❖ Dog park and spa ❖ Dry cleaning lockers ❖ Next to the Waterfront Metro station ❖ Package acceptance ❖ Resident lounge ❖ Rooftop deck with grills and pool ❖ Shared workspace with printing ❖ Air conditioning ❖ Granite countertops ❖ Open-concept layout ❖ Plank flooring ❖ Stainless steel appliances ❖ Tile backsplash ❖ Washer and dryer in-home Pets: We understand pets are a huge part of good living. Lex & Leo at Waterfront Station welcomes both cats and dogs in our apartment homes. We also have a dog park and pet spa so your furry friends can live the good life too. Note we do have some restrictions please view our full pet policy below. We welcome cats and dogs!* Pet move-in fee: $500 Per dog monthly fee: $55 Per cat monthly fee: $55 *Maximum of two pets per apartment. Breed restrictions may apply. Business Hours: Tue - Fri: 9:00 AM - 6:00 PM Sat: 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM Sun: 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM Ready to Lease? Reach out via phone or text: show contact info Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/LexandLeoApartments Website: www.apt-rental.com?n=leo_at_waterfront_station&rp=mEWgikUf2pUb&t=wb Schedule a Tour: www.apt-rental.com?n=leo_at_waterfront_station&rp=mEWgikUf2pUb&t=sch * Pricing, specials and availability are subject to change without notice and may be subject to specific lease terms and other conditions. Contact leasing associate for details. Bernstein Management Corporation will not refuse to rent a rental unit to a person because the person will provide the rental payment, in whole or in part, through a voucher for rental housing assistance provided as applicable by the District, state, or federal government. Equal Housing Opportunity. All pricing, availability, fees, and terms are subject to change without notice. EQUAL HOUSING OPPORTUNITY 47433F018AEE4D82",
